  "prompt": "What are some really good Korean spas in Minneapolis?",
  "response": "Minneapolis has a few options if you're looking for a Korean spa experience, although the options might not be as abundant as in larger metropolitan areas like Los Angeles or New York. Here are some suggestions you might consider:\n\n1. **Jinjer Spa** - Located in Edina, just outside Minneapolis, Jinjer Spa offers services inspired by traditional Korean beauty and wellness treatments.\n\n2. **King Spa & Sauna** - Although not directly in Minneapolis, this spa in nearby Illinois is a notable Korean-style spa that offers a range of saunas and traditional treatments. It could be a good choice for a weekend getaway.\n\n3. **Spa Land** - Another option outside Minneapolis, often praised for its traditional Korean treatments, saunas, and relaxation areas.\n\nIf you're specifically after a true Korean spa experience with jjimjilbang-style amenities, you may need to look at nearby cities or be open to travel. Always check recent reviews and contact the spas directly to ensure they offer the services you're looking for, as offerings can change.",
